Game.Name: Sightwaves
Game.Description:
This was our submission for Global Game Jam 2017, the first game jam that we participated in. It was developed by John Wolfson, Will Dixon and Daniel Dennis at the University of Lincoln.
The theme of this jam was Waves. With this we came up with the idea of the player not being able to see through traditional means but, instead seeing the world through sound. So as a player, you need to make noise in order to perceive the world around you. Find your way through abandoned structures and solve puzzles in order to find your way back home.

Game.Name: The Lone Astronaut
Game.Description:
This was out submission for Global Game Jam 2018. It was developed by John Wolfson, Will Dixon, Daniel Dennis, Tim Weightman and Luke Garside at the University of Lincoln.
The theme for this jam was Transmission. With this in mind and inspiration from 'The Martian', we came up with the idea of the player being trapped on the planet Mars and needing to complete many different puzzles and problems in order to escape back home to Earth.

Game.Name: Time To Kill
Game.Description:
This was our submission for CanJam 2017. It was developed by John Wolfson, Will Dixon, Daniel Dennis, Tim Weightman and Luke Garside at the University of Lincoln.
The theme for this jam was Time. With this we came up with the concept of time speeding up or slowing down based on the players ability. Shoot your way past your enemies to get to the bomb at the end of each stage to disarm it before it blows you all to kingdom come.

Game.Name: Revenge of Johny 5
Game.Description:
This was our submission for CanJam 2018. It was developed by John Wolfson, Will Dixon, Tim Weightman and Luke Garside at the University of Lincoln.
The theme for this jam was Surprisingly Spooky. Navigate an abandoned labratory be wary not to be caught by the ruthless murdering robot patrolling its corridors. Collect the three different parts of the EMP before escaping to put an end to his rampage and uncover the mystery of what happened to the staff along the way.

Game.Name: Home Is Where The Mech Is
Game.Description:
This is our game that we made for Global Game Jam 2019, but with an addition of an Offline mode.
The game is a first person shooter where you need to defend your home with your mech! It features twitch integration for streamers so that the Twitch chat can choose and spawn your enemies, or if you prefer this version features has an offline mode.
*Twitch mode is currently broken due to changes in the API*

Game.Name: Lunarstein
Game.Description:
This our submission for CanJam 2019 which was a game jam hosted by the Games Development Society at University of Lincoln!
The evil Computer Science Society has started to use technology for evil! Only the Game Development Society stands between them and total domination!
Progress your way through their spaceship, destroying their generators to bring their ship down to the moons surface, before fighting your way to their rocket to make your escape!

Game.Name: PURRRPETRATOR
Game.Description:
Game made for SpookJam 2019. THEME: Hidden Below
A 2D platformer in which you play as a playful ginger cat who is stuck inside a Egyptian Crypt. You have to do your best as a cat and knock over as many Egyptians pots as possible before you get sucked back in by Anubis! The game features platforming aspects with chase AI that will disrupt you along your pot smashing adventure. The project can be played on both Keyboard & Mouse and Controller.

Game.Name: Repair-a-bots
Game.Description:
Help out your bigger bot friend so he can take down the evil robot monsters that are hidden around the world. A simple top-down coop exploration-based game with heavy-hitting combat and unforgiving battles. Your 3 friends will need to aid you by picking up scrap to heal you, boost you and make you hit a little harder.
Players: 1-4

Game.Name: Lost Castle
Game.Description:
This is our game that we made for Global Game Jam 2021!
Your castle has been taken from you, you need to sneak in to take back your gold, sword and free your friends! Don't let the guards see you, once the alarm is raised more guards will come hunting for your head!

Game.Name: Meiyo Doggo
Game.Description:
You are forced out of Samurai retirement after a barbaric attack on your childhood village, resulting in the hunt of a lifetime for man's best friend.
GAME WORKS BEST WITH AN XBOX CONTROLLER
